<p>
  <span class="nym">Indigo</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">English</span> <i>indico, indigo</i> from <span class="lang">Latin</span> <i>indicum</i>, <span class="lang">Greek</span> <i>ἰνδικόν</i> 'Indian', used to refer to blue Indian dye.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>This word for the dye only came into use in England in the 16th C; it is extremely unusual to find it used as a given name.</p>
</div>
  


